This paper discusses issues related to explainable AI, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the concerns of different types of users, including lay users, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper analyzes the adequacy of existing explanation methods, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the General Data Protection Regulation, which relates to cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY), and addresses concerns about bias and unfair outcomes, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
